"^yellow;Chapter 4: Practical Applications^reset;

The first step in creating mistakes is creating ^green;distractions!^reset;

From spotlights to spike pits, it's important that intruders always have something interesting or provocative to look at to keep their focus away from the traps intended to cripple them or finish them off.

^red;Monsters, ^yellow;shiny objects, ^reset;and ^green;baited chests^reset; are all effective distractions!
^#8888CC;>>",

"^yellow;Chapter 4: Practical Applications^reset;

The second step in creating mistakes is creating ^green;syncopation!^reset;

If you're not familiar with this funny word, syncopation is when something occurs that's off-rhythm or off-beat. ^green;Most species struggle with arrythmic timings,^reset; and even the faintest patterns, like the soft pulses of a crystal lamp, can have a huge impact on the potency of a surprise attack.

^#8888CC;>>",

